ACI - Application Centric Infrastructure

Datacenter Automation

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Application Centric Policies are very important

Nexus 9K Fabric - auto configures devices based on policies

All connection in Nexus 9K fabric (guts of the data center) are constructed in a spine-leaf architecture

All connections are layer 3 from device to device that all share interior protocol (ospf, bgp, eigrp, is-is, etc.)

VXLAN - carries VLAN & layer 2 information in the layer 3 packet to central application - leading to full L2 connectivity across all data center devices

APIC Controller - Application Policy Infrastructure Controller - provides the brain for all the data centers - how to configure devices.

IS-IS (Intermediate System) - underlay protocol

VXLAN - Overlay protocol

3 physical servers running APIC - make all the magic happen, provide brains & automation for all of the data center

- How devices know how to configure themselves (policy-based)
- Not part of data plane (data thats being passed) or control plane (how devices determine which routes to use)
- They are part of the management plane - utilized from frontend GUI

ACI allows multi-tenants where each tenant has different infrastructures

Always a tenant called "common"

Uni is root level of ACI

Then we can have multiple tenants - common tenant can apply global rules

EPGs - End Point groups - similar servers sharing endpoints i.e. database servers

Contracts - fundamental to ACI - everything must have a contract to communicate in ACI

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Bridge Domains are layer 2 VLANs connected to EPGs.
